  "prompt": "If somebody is smoking weed around me, is it possible to get high off of second hand smoke?",
  "response": "Yes, it is possible to get high from secondhand cannabis smoke, although the likelihood and intensity of the effect can vary based on several factors. These include the potency of the cannabis, the volume of smoke in the air, the duration of exposure, and the ventilation of the area where the smoke is present.\n\nIn general, being in a poorly ventilated space with a significant amount of cannabis smoke can increase the chances of experiencing secondhand effects. However, in most casual encounters, such as being in a well-ventilated room where someone is smoking some distance away, the effects are usually minimal or negligible. If you are concerned about exposure, ensuring good ventilation or removing yourself from the environment can help reduce the risk of any unwanted effects.",
